      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The fact that CCTV shows no theft suggests these \"disappearances\" are likely due to subtle operational processes rather than malicious intent, such as items being moved for maintenance, rework, or quality control without a corresponding system update. It is also possible that the electronic components are being returned to a supplier for rework or exchange, a process that might be logged in a separate system or manually recorded and not reflected in the main inventory count. Another subtle possibility is that the items are being used for testing or prototyping in the R&D department and then returned without an immediate adjustment to the warehouse stock levels. To address this, I recommend reviewing the internal transfer logs and the R&D department's inventory reconciliation procedures to ensure all movements are captured in the central system.",
